1
00:00:07,721 --> 00:00:09,481
[If you don't turn yourself in,
your limbs will rot and you'll die]

2
00:00:37,938 --> 00:00:41,038
[All characters and events are fictional,
and any resemblance is coincidental]

3
00:00:41,038 --> 00:00:43,438
[Scenes with children and animals were filmed
safely under professional supervision]

4
00:00:43,438 --> 00:00:46,005
Nice to meet you.

5
00:00:46,005 --> 00:00:47,638
Have a seat.

6
00:00:49,838 --> 00:00:51,472
Come in.

7
00:00:58,372 --> 00:01:00,238
Father, I'm here.

8
00:01:01,472 --> 00:01:03,272
It's your second brother.

9
00:01:07,405 --> 00:01:10,738
How did my child end up fatherless
before even being born?

10
00:01:11,472 --> 00:01:16,605
I have no intention of letting my child
live as family with that man.

11
00:01:19,972 --> 00:01:22,338
I won't live as your daughter.

12
00:01:24,138 --> 00:01:25,772
Sun...

13
00:01:36,538 --> 00:01:39,805
<i>Tae Joo, Sun Young was in a car accident.</i>

14
00:01:39,805 --> 00:01:42,405
<i>You need to come quickly.</i>

15
00:01:54,538 --> 00:01:56,172
Sun Young!

16
00:01:58,005 --> 00:02:01,305
Sun Young, it's me.

17
00:02:01,305 --> 00:02:02,905
I'm here.

18
00:02:03,705 --> 00:02:05,538
Open your eyes.

19
00:02:07,005 --> 00:02:08,605
Sun Young...

20
00:02:12,638 --> 00:02:15,305
The baby's been delivered.

21
00:02:15,305 --> 00:02:17,238
The baby's in the incubator now.

22
00:02:20,005 --> 00:02:22,238
The baby's okay, right?

23
00:02:22,238 --> 00:02:23,505
They can't guarantee that.

24
00:02:23,505 --> 00:02:25,805
The baby was delivered before 7 months.

25
00:02:25,805 --> 00:02:28,772
We don't know yet whether there'll be
complications or disabilities later on.

26
00:02:28,772 --> 00:02:29,772
What about Sun Young?

27
00:02:29,772 --> 00:02:32,305
She suffered severe head trauma.

28
00:02:32,305 --> 00:02:35,172
They've barely managed to
stop the critical bleeding.

29
00:02:40,405 --> 00:02:43,305
Do you know why she got into that accident?

30
00:02:43,305 --> 00:02:45,641
She ended up like this

31
00:02:45,641 --> 00:02:47,705
trying to run away to you.

32
00:02:47,705 --> 00:02:49,672
How can you even say that right now?

33
00:02:49,672 --> 00:02:52,772
Who was it that suddenly showed up
and turned her life upside down?

34
00:02:52,772 --> 00:02:56,305
If you hadn't interfered,
she never would've ended up like this.

35
00:02:57,283 --> 00:02:58,729
Fine,

36
00:02:59,438 --> 00:03:01,772
then make your choice.

37
00:03:01,772 --> 00:03:07,405
If you want to keep living as her brother
like you always have, so be it.

38
00:03:07,405 --> 00:03:09,005
And then

39
00:03:10,938 --> 00:03:12,872
I'll give up on her.

40
00:03:12,872 --> 00:03:15,172
Then leave, right now.

41
00:03:29,005 --> 00:03:30,638
Let's go.

42
00:03:32,038 --> 00:03:33,672
Father.

43
00:03:34,338 --> 00:03:37,305
Father, wait, Father...

44
00:03:37,305 --> 00:03:39,038
Please wake up.

45
00:03:39,038 --> 00:03:41,038
Tae Joo, you need to think this through.

46
00:03:41,038 --> 00:03:42,905
Only my father can save
Sun Young now, not you.

47
00:03:42,905 --> 00:03:44,972
Shut up and get lost.

48
00:03:55,405 --> 00:03:57,572
Sun Young!

49
00:03:57,572 --> 00:03:59,505
- Nurse!
- Sun Young!

50
00:03:59,505 --> 00:04:01,738
Sun Young, wake up!

51
00:04:01,738 --> 00:04:04,838
What do we do?

52
00:04:08,505 --> 00:04:10,249
Doctor,

53
00:04:10,249 --> 00:04:11,372
what happened?

54
00:04:11,372 --> 00:04:13,005
It appears a blood vessel
in her brain has ruptured.

55
00:04:13,005 --> 00:04:14,538
She needs surgery immediately.

56
00:04:14,538 --> 00:04:17,305
But we don't have a surgeon
capable of performing it here.

57
00:04:17,305 --> 00:04:20,272
What do we do then?
We have to transfer her to another hospital.

58
00:04:20,272 --> 00:04:22,338
It'll be too late by then.

59
00:04:22,338 --> 00:04:26,105
I heard Assemblyman Cha called
in a surgeon. Don't you know about it?

60
00:04:26,105 --> 00:04:27,738
I...

61
00:04:34,338 --> 00:04:37,338
Father, Tae Joo is here.

62
00:04:44,872 --> 00:04:47,005
Please save Sun Young.

63
00:04:52,038 --> 00:04:53,638
Father!

64
00:04:54,838 --> 00:04:56,472
Please save her.

65
00:04:57,505 --> 00:04:59,138
If you save her,

66
00:05:00,438 --> 00:05:02,272
I'll do anything.

67
00:05:04,638 --> 00:05:06,672
Anything?

68
00:05:13,272 --> 00:05:15,205
Leave Kangseng.

69
00:05:15,938 --> 00:05:17,972
Never show your face in Kangseng ever again.

70
00:05:17,972 --> 00:05:19,805
Not in front of me,

71
00:05:19,805 --> 00:05:22,405
my family, or Sun Young.

72
00:05:25,705 --> 00:05:27,972
Can you promise that?

73
00:05:30,105 --> 00:05:32,105
I promise.

74
00:05:37,205 --> 00:05:39,005
I promise.

75
00:05:41,272 --> 00:05:44,838
[Muil Inn]

76
00:05:54,405 --> 00:05:56,105
Kang Tae Joo!

77
00:05:58,705 --> 00:06:01,838
You're really leaving like this? Seriously?

78
00:06:03,505 --> 00:06:05,438
Sun Young's still in a coma.

79
00:06:05,438 --> 00:06:08,172
And the killer still hasn't been caught.

80
00:06:11,638 --> 00:06:13,472
I'm sorry.

81
00:06:13,472 --> 00:06:15,105
Tae Joo!

82
00:06:16,072 --> 00:06:17,705
Why? Hey.

83
00:06:17,705 --> 00:06:19,572
Hey, tell me! Why?

84
00:06:19,572 --> 00:06:21,172
Hurry up and tell me.

85
00:06:21,172 --> 00:06:25,372
Tell me. There has to be
a reason you're doing this.

86
00:06:25,372 --> 00:06:26,972
Ji Won.

87
00:06:29,238 --> 00:06:31,672
Honestly, I used to laugh at that punk.

88
00:06:32,705 --> 00:06:35,172
A pathetic coward

89
00:06:35,172 --> 00:06:38,972
hiding behind a scarecrow and killing people.

90
00:06:38,972 --> 00:06:41,105
I thought I'd catch him in no time.

91
00:06:41,972 --> 00:06:45,972
I thought we'd catch him quickly
and leave Kangseng behind.

92
00:06:47,505 --> 00:06:49,738
But now,

93
00:06:54,005 --> 00:06:56,572
there's nothing more I can do.

94
00:06:57,905 --> 00:06:59,538
Nothing.

95
00:07:01,138 --> 00:07:03,672
I don't even know
who's the scarecrow anymore.

96
00:07:11,872 --> 00:07:14,038
Kang Tae Joo, listen carefully.

97
00:07:16,072 --> 00:07:18,672
If you leave like this,

98
00:07:20,772 --> 00:07:23,238
I'll never see you again.

99
00:07:27,338 --> 00:07:29,072
Never.

100
00:07:31,305 --> 00:07:32,905
I'm sorry.

101
00:07:34,005 --> 00:07:35,638
Really.

102
00:08:20,105 --> 00:08:22,305
That took longer than expected.

103
00:08:23,405 --> 00:08:25,289
I thought you were actually dead.

104
00:08:25,289 --> 00:08:26,872
You punk!

105
00:08:26,872 --> 00:08:28,338
Tae Joo,

106
00:08:28,338 --> 00:08:30,972
I'm telling you this as a friend.

107
00:08:30,972 --> 00:08:33,472
Do what Si Young says.

108
00:08:33,472 --> 00:08:37,972
Otherwise, next time, you could really
end up buried alive without a trace.

109
00:08:37,972 --> 00:08:40,572
You need to think about your sister too.

110
00:09:11,038 --> 00:09:13,513
[Episode 11]

111
00:09:29,138 --> 00:09:31,005
[Murder 12+2]
One of these two is a child,

112
00:09:31,005 --> 00:09:35,072
and what do you think the other one is?

113
00:09:35,072 --> 00:09:36,938
Want a hint?

114
00:09:39,238 --> 00:09:40,681
It's another

115
00:09:40,681 --> 00:09:43,372
very unfortunate case.

116
00:09:43,372 --> 00:09:45,225
Because

117
00:09:45,225 --> 00:09:48,472
the wrong person was arrested in my place.

118
00:09:48,472 --> 00:09:52,305
And you're the one

119
00:09:52,305 --> 00:09:53,938
who put him

120
00:09:55,405 --> 00:09:57,505
behind bars.

121
00:09:57,505 --> 00:10:00,072
Don't tell me the 7th case...

122
00:10:01,072 --> 00:10:02,672
Right.

123
00:10:04,072 --> 00:10:06,238
I did that too.

124
00:10:24,272 --> 00:10:25,572
Chief, I brought it.

125
00:10:25,572 --> 00:10:28,772
Jeez, I asked for this ages ago.

126
00:10:28,772 --> 00:10:30,572
Huh? Why only one?

127
00:10:30,572 --> 00:10:32,005
I told you two boxes of parts.

128
00:10:32,005 --> 00:10:33,305
I thought you said one box...

129
00:10:33,305 --> 00:10:36,438
If you're slow on your feet,
at least have decent hearing.

130
00:10:36,438 --> 00:10:37,972
I said two! Two!

131
00:10:37,972 --> 00:10:40,472
I'm sorry. I'll go get the rest.

132
00:10:43,372 --> 00:10:46,938
What? I heard he had an ex-con,
but he was a sex offender too?

133
00:10:46,938 --> 00:10:48,238
I heard he even killed someone.

134
00:10:48,238 --> 00:10:49,938
That guy's a real piece of work.

135
00:10:49,938 --> 00:10:52,205
Just get back to work.

136
00:11:23,305 --> 00:11:24,905
Seok Man.

137
00:11:35,505 --> 00:11:37,372
Tae Joo?

138
00:11:38,805 --> 00:11:40,405
Do you

139
00:11:41,038 --> 00:11:42,972
remember me?

140
00:11:45,438 --> 00:11:47,038
Seok Man!

141
00:11:48,038 --> 00:11:49,538
Why are you here?

142
00:11:49,538 --> 00:11:51,772
What are you trying to pin on me this time?

143
00:11:53,805 --> 00:11:55,505
Do you live alone?

144
00:11:57,005 --> 00:11:59,005
No family with you?

145
00:11:59,005 --> 00:12:01,472
Who would want to live
with an ex-con like me?

146
00:12:01,472 --> 00:12:03,172
If you've got something to say,
say it and leave!

147
00:12:03,172 --> 00:12:05,772
Stop making my life harder!

148
00:12:06,572 --> 00:12:08,205
Seok Man,

149
00:12:08,205 --> 00:12:11,138
have you heard they caught

150
00:12:11,138 --> 00:12:14,005
the real Kangseng serial killer?

151
00:12:14,005 --> 00:12:16,638
What's that got to do with me?

152
00:12:16,638 --> 00:12:18,538
That real killer

153
00:12:20,738 --> 00:12:24,305
confessed that the seventh case
was also his doing.

154
00:12:26,738 --> 00:12:28,872
Is that

155
00:12:28,872 --> 00:12:30,805
really true?

156
00:12:31,772 --> 00:12:33,372
Yeah.

157
00:12:39,138 --> 00:12:45,305
I told you... I told you it wasn't me.

158
00:12:47,238 --> 00:12:52,605
I kept saying I was innocent. But why...

159
00:12:54,005 --> 00:12:56,472
You should've trusted me back then.

160
00:12:56,472 --> 00:12:59,638
Why bring this up now?

161
00:12:59,638 --> 00:13:00,638
I'm sorry.

162
00:13:00,638 --> 00:13:03,838
You made me live as a murderer
for over thirty years,

163
00:13:03,838 --> 00:13:07,305
and why now...

164
00:13:30,905 --> 00:13:32,538
I...

165
00:13:33,672 --> 00:13:36,672
I committed an unforgivable sin against you.

166
00:13:37,572 --> 00:13:38,872
I'm sorry.

167
00:13:38,872 --> 00:13:41,705
What's the point of saying that now?

168
00:13:42,805 --> 00:13:46,472
Can you give me my life back?

169
00:13:47,372 --> 00:13:50,572
I lost my family, my friends,

170
00:13:50,572 --> 00:13:53,225
and my youth, everything.

171
00:13:53,225 --> 00:13:55,505
But why now?

172
00:13:58,638 --> 00:14:01,438
You shouldn't have told me at all.

173
00:14:02,372 --> 00:14:05,172
You should've just let me
keep living without knowing.

174
00:14:06,072 --> 00:14:07,772
I'm sorry...

175
00:14:13,105 --> 00:14:15,105
Truly sorry.

176
00:14:20,538 --> 00:14:23,272
What kind of person is he?

177
00:14:23,272 --> 00:14:25,005
The killer, I mean.

178
00:14:27,638 --> 00:14:29,673
Lee Ki Hwan.

179
00:14:29,673 --> 00:14:31,209
Remember him?

180
00:14:32,038 --> 00:14:33,672
Ki Beom's brother.

181
00:14:34,738 --> 00:14:36,872
No way...

182
00:14:36,872 --> 00:14:39,272
Ki Beom's brother is the killer?

183
00:14:49,505 --> 00:14:51,738
What kind of brother does that?

184
00:14:51,738 --> 00:14:57,205
His younger brother took the fall
and went to prison, and he just watched?

185
00:14:58,472 --> 00:15:02,005
Ki Beom adored his brother so much.

186
00:15:03,105 --> 00:15:06,038
And he was your friend too!

187
00:15:06,038 --> 00:15:08,672
How could you not notice?

188
00:15:09,438 --> 00:15:11,705
I have no excuse.

189
00:15:13,538 --> 00:15:15,538
It's so unfair.

190
00:15:15,538 --> 00:15:18,372
I'm going crazy from how unfair this is.

191
00:15:21,738 --> 00:15:25,705
Of course, you're angry and resentful.

192
00:15:26,638 --> 00:15:29,138
But we still have to set things right.

193
00:15:30,305 --> 00:15:31,938
Seok Man.

194
00:15:34,038 --> 00:15:36,172
Let's file for a retrial.

195
00:15:39,672 --> 00:15:44,172
[Attorney Cha Yeon Ho's Office]

196
00:15:49,138 --> 00:15:52,338
I think this is strong enough to go for it.

197
00:15:52,338 --> 00:15:53,338
Really?

198
00:15:53,338 --> 00:15:56,505
The torture during the confession process
was clearly illegal.

199
00:15:56,505 --> 00:16:01,572
Makes no sense to get a handwritten statement
from someone who can't even read or write.

200
00:16:01,572 --> 00:16:04,805
Most importantly, the real killer confessed,

201
00:16:04,805 --> 00:16:06,772
so it's looking pretty good for us.

202
00:16:16,672 --> 00:16:21,338
[Female body found in Kangseng County]

203
00:16:22,405 --> 00:16:26,405
[Exclusive photo of the Kangseng
serial killer obtained]

204
00:16:26,405 --> 00:16:28,938
[Photo of the Suspect]

205
00:16:33,138 --> 00:16:34,138
[Murder 12+2]

206
00:16:34,138 --> 00:16:35,438
12 plus 2.

207
00:16:35,438 --> 00:16:38,438
Lee Yong Woo confessed to 14 cases in total.

208
00:16:38,438 --> 00:16:42,172
Aside from the nine known
Kangseng serial murders,

209
00:16:42,172 --> 00:16:45,372
these three are included in the "12."

210
00:16:45,372 --> 00:16:47,172
Two happened in Cheongju,

211
00:16:47,172 --> 00:16:49,338
and one in Muwon.

212
00:16:51,072 --> 00:16:52,605
And he confessed to the extra two as well?

213
00:16:52,605 --> 00:16:55,772
Yes, one of them involves

214
00:16:55,772 --> 00:16:57,538
an eight-year-old girl named Yoon Hye Jin...

215
00:16:57,538 --> 00:16:59,538
Wait.

216
00:16:59,538 --> 00:17:01,372
Who? Yoon Hye Jin?

217
00:17:01,372 --> 00:17:03,438
- Yes.
- Do you know about the case?

218
00:17:04,205 --> 00:17:07,038
Yeah, when I was at Kangseng Daily,

219
00:17:07,038 --> 00:17:10,672
her parents placed an ad in the paper
looking for the missing girl.

220
00:17:10,672 --> 00:17:12,205
They even showed up on TV.

221
00:17:12,205 --> 00:17:16,372
That's right. They appeared on
"Inside the National Police Agency" in 1988.

222
00:17:16,372 --> 00:17:17,542
Oh, dear.

223
00:17:18,153 --> 00:17:20,338
So this is how it ended.

224
00:17:21,672 --> 00:17:23,272
What about the other one?

225
00:17:23,272 --> 00:17:25,705
Well...

226
00:17:27,105 --> 00:17:29,172
It's the 7th case.

227
00:17:29,172 --> 00:17:31,238
The 7th case? The copycat one?

228
00:17:31,238 --> 00:17:32,681
Yes.

229
00:17:32,681 --> 00:17:34,672
That turned out to be Lee Yong Woo too.

230
00:17:34,672 --> 00:17:38,038
But that man already served
twenty years in prison.

231
00:17:39,638 --> 00:17:41,472
As expected of our center director,

232
00:17:41,472 --> 00:17:43,705
you really do have incredible instincts.

233
00:17:44,472 --> 00:17:47,205
So that's why you had
the rookie investigate it.

234
00:17:47,205 --> 00:17:49,172
How did you know?

235
00:17:50,538 --> 00:17:52,272
But,

236
00:17:52,972 --> 00:17:57,372
why call it 12 plus 2 instead of 14?

237
00:17:57,372 --> 00:17:59,405
Now that you mention it, why indeed?

238
00:18:00,172 --> 00:18:03,872
Why were only those two cases separated out?

239
00:18:08,738 --> 00:18:11,105
Jang Myeong Do and Do Hyeong Gu
already retired.

240
00:18:11,105 --> 00:18:13,938
And Park Dae Ho is still active.

241
00:18:13,938 --> 00:18:16,572
Plus, the prosecutor in charge
is now a sitting assemblyman.

242
00:18:16,572 --> 00:18:19,805
What happens if they all
deny the allegations?

243
00:18:19,805 --> 00:18:23,872
Well, isn't there at least one person
among them who can be persuaded?

244
00:18:26,672 --> 00:18:30,705
You have a lunch appointment
with Assemblyman Woo Sang Hoon.

245
00:18:30,705 --> 00:18:32,305
Cha Si Young!

246
00:18:40,272 --> 00:18:41,872
Sir?

247
00:18:45,038 --> 00:18:49,272
Well, look who's here.

248
00:18:50,372 --> 00:18:52,072
Kang Tae Joo!

249
00:18:54,738 --> 00:18:58,672
Wow, it's been forever.

250
00:18:58,672 --> 00:19:00,393
You two go on ahead.

251
00:19:00,393 --> 00:19:02,672
I'll catch up with my old friend.

252
00:19:09,305 --> 00:19:10,938
Jeez.

253
00:19:12,305 --> 00:19:16,505
I catch your TV program sometimes.

254
00:19:16,505 --> 00:19:18,441
Profiler?

255
00:19:18,441 --> 00:19:19,971
Wow.

256
00:19:20,872 --> 00:19:22,838
It suits you.

257
00:19:25,138 --> 00:19:29,205
You heard they caught
the real Kangseng serial killer, right?

258
00:19:30,121 --> 00:19:32,805
Of course, I did.

259
00:19:33,472 --> 00:19:38,538
Life really is strange.

260
00:19:38,538 --> 00:19:42,672
He never showed up when we were
desperately searching for him,

261
00:19:42,672 --> 00:19:45,138
but now that everyone's
almost forgotten about it,

262
00:19:45,138 --> 00:19:47,172
he finally appears.

263
00:19:48,905 --> 00:19:51,938
Guess this is what they call karma
catching up in the end.

264
00:19:51,938 --> 00:19:54,372
We're still far
from true justice being served.

265
00:19:54,372 --> 00:19:56,169
Well then,

266
00:19:56,169 --> 00:19:58,772
why don't you try making
that happen yourself?

267
00:19:59,505 --> 00:20:00,538
What are you talking about?

268
00:20:00,538 --> 00:20:02,377
The real killer

269
00:20:02,377 --> 00:20:04,805
confessed to everything.

270
00:20:04,805 --> 00:20:07,805
Including Im Seok Man's case
and Yoon Hye Jin's.

271
00:20:10,038 --> 00:20:12,172
Yoon Hye Jin?

272
00:20:12,172 --> 00:20:14,472
The girl you buried.

273
00:20:20,138 --> 00:20:23,072
Now, it's your turn to tell the truth.

274
00:20:28,649 --> 00:20:31,538
I have no idea what you are talking about.

275
00:20:31,538 --> 00:20:33,038
Wait, Cha Si Young.

276
00:20:33,038 --> 00:20:34,638
Uncle!

277
00:20:37,472 --> 00:20:39,072
<i>Ki Beom?</i>

278
00:20:43,072 --> 00:20:45,138
- Yeah.
- Uncle, there you are.

279
00:20:46,905 --> 00:20:50,938
Hey, you brat. You should've
told me you were coming!

280
00:20:50,938 --> 00:20:53,138
I'll come up after I see my guest off.

281
00:20:53,138 --> 00:20:55,105
You go on ahead.

282
00:20:58,172 --> 00:20:59,572
Huh?

283
00:20:59,572 --> 00:21:02,205
You're Profiler Kang Tae Joo, right?

284
00:21:02,205 --> 00:21:03,738
Yes.

285
00:21:03,738 --> 00:21:07,638
If I'd known you were my uncle's acquaintance,
I would've come to see you sooner.

286
00:21:08,838 --> 00:21:10,738
I'm Cha Young Beom.

287
00:21:12,572 --> 00:21:13,605
Professor,

288
00:21:13,605 --> 00:21:15,672
[Cha Young Beom, Noise Cut Intern]
I'm a huge fan.

289
00:21:17,205 --> 00:21:18,938
Cha Young Beom.

290
00:21:20,705 --> 00:21:22,338
Nice to meet you.

291
00:21:22,338 --> 00:21:23,472
Alright, alright.

292
00:21:23,472 --> 00:21:25,172
Go on up ahead.

293
00:21:39,272 --> 00:21:41,238
What brings you here?

294
00:21:41,238 --> 00:21:43,672
Our appointment time is still a long way off.

295
00:21:43,672 --> 00:21:46,438
I was nearby, so I stopped by.
I have some time to kill.

296
00:21:46,438 --> 00:21:47,438
[Assemblyman Cha Si Young]

297
00:21:47,438 --> 00:21:48,672
Do you think I'm free all day?

298
00:21:48,672 --> 00:21:51,905
I know, our assemblyman's a very busy person.

299
00:21:51,905 --> 00:21:54,572
But what could I do? I wanted to see you.

300
00:21:54,572 --> 00:21:56,506
What?

301
00:21:59,497 --> 00:22:01,705
By the way, Uncle,

302
00:22:01,705 --> 00:22:04,005
how do you know Professor Kang Tae Joo?

303
00:22:05,738 --> 00:22:07,672
Know him?

304
00:22:07,672 --> 00:22:11,805
I just ran into him by chance,
for the first time in thirty years.

305
00:22:11,805 --> 00:22:14,538
But why? What's with Kang Tae Joo?

306
00:22:14,538 --> 00:22:16,172
Well...

307
00:22:18,972 --> 00:22:21,705
[Assemblyman Cha Si Young]
Uncle, I need to take this call.

308
00:22:23,172 --> 00:22:24,805
Yes, hello?

309
00:22:26,805 --> 00:22:28,438
[Assemblyman's Office]
Oh, Mr. Min.

310
00:22:39,205 --> 00:22:40,638
<i>Yoon Hye Jin?</i>

311
00:22:40,638 --> 00:22:42,938
<i>The girl you buried.</i>

312
00:22:51,538 --> 00:22:52,805
I don't have any more
appointments today, right?

313
00:22:52,805 --> 00:22:54,838
You have dinner plans
with your family tonight.

314
00:22:54,838 --> 00:22:57,038
With your son
and your older brother's family.

315
00:22:57,938 --> 00:22:59,472
Did I make that appointment?

316
00:22:59,472 --> 00:23:03,138
It's your birthday today, so your son
asked me to arrange dinner.

317
00:23:03,138 --> 00:23:05,972
I already informed you, Chairwoman.

318
00:23:05,972 --> 00:23:07,638
Anyway, got it.

319
00:23:28,938 --> 00:23:31,138
I recently joined a media company.

320
00:23:31,805 --> 00:23:33,838
It's been about two months.

321
00:23:33,838 --> 00:23:35,638
Which media company?

322
00:23:35,638 --> 00:23:38,405
It's called Noise Cut.
It's an independent media outlet.

323
00:23:40,438 --> 00:23:42,405
Did you know about it?

324
00:23:43,272 --> 00:23:45,305
I heard recently.

325
00:23:50,025 --> 00:23:53,738
Some place nobody's ever heard of...

326
00:23:54,857 --> 00:23:59,638
If I'd known this would happen,
I'd have inherited Kangseng Daily.

327
00:23:59,638 --> 00:24:02,772
I could've given it to Young Beom, right?

328
00:24:02,772 --> 00:24:05,672
I'm more suited to this kind of work
than legacy media.

329
00:24:05,672 --> 00:24:09,972
Honestly, you're something else.

330
00:24:10,705 --> 00:24:12,605
Who does he take after?

331
00:24:12,605 --> 00:24:14,938
Who does he get this from?

332
00:24:15,605 --> 00:24:19,205
Definitely not from you, Sun Young.

333
00:24:21,405 --> 00:24:23,372
Must be his father.

334
00:24:23,372 --> 00:24:25,005
Honey!

335
00:24:31,272 --> 00:24:33,905
I even got assigned
an exclusive article this time.

336
00:24:33,905 --> 00:24:36,672
It's related to the Kangseng serial murders.

337
00:24:36,672 --> 00:24:38,872
What article?

338
00:24:38,872 --> 00:24:40,938
Not exactly the serial murder case itself,

339
00:24:40,938 --> 00:24:43,505
- but one of them, the 7th case...
- Drop it.

340
00:24:45,641 --> 00:24:49,338
Well, now that they've
caught the real killer,

341
00:24:49,338 --> 00:24:51,605
they must be digging around
for sensational stories.

342
00:24:51,605 --> 00:24:53,405
No, it's not like that.

343
00:24:53,405 --> 00:24:55,305
Young Beom,

344
00:24:55,305 --> 00:24:56,838
I should get going.

345
00:24:56,838 --> 00:24:59,105
I have an important appointment later.

346
00:24:59,105 --> 00:25:00,745
Sun Young,

347
00:25:00,745 --> 00:25:02,938
I genuinely wish you a happy birthday.

348
00:25:02,938 --> 00:25:04,405
Thank you.

349
00:25:04,405 --> 00:25:05,972
But we haven't finished eating.

350
00:25:05,972 --> 00:25:09,638
Then pack it and take it home.

351
00:25:15,538 --> 00:25:17,705
I'll see Auntie off and come back.

352
00:25:26,005 --> 00:25:28,205
Are you seriously just going to
leave Young Beom like this?

353
00:25:28,205 --> 00:25:31,172
No matter how busy
you're with the foundation,

354
00:25:31,172 --> 00:25:33,738
if you'd paid proper attention to him...

355
00:25:37,472 --> 00:25:39,105
Why?

356
00:25:41,072 --> 00:25:44,372
Are you afraid Young Beom
might find something?

357
00:25:45,572 --> 00:25:47,401
Young Beom

358
00:25:47,401 --> 00:25:50,438
might go see Kang Tae Joo soon.

359
00:26:11,172 --> 00:26:15,205
[Searching for the Missing]

360
00:26:15,205 --> 00:26:17,672
What are you talking about?

361
00:26:17,672 --> 00:26:18,972
How could the police...

362
00:26:18,972 --> 00:26:24,538
Father, don't just sit there silently.
Say something!

363
00:26:24,538 --> 00:26:26,249
Back then,

364
00:26:26,249 --> 00:26:30,072
I should've listened to those words.

365
00:26:30,072 --> 00:26:33,738
30 years ago, you said it, right?

366
00:26:33,738 --> 00:26:36,172
[Searching for the Missing]

367
00:26:37,672 --> 00:26:40,172
That our Hye Jin is dead...

368
00:26:49,905 --> 00:26:52,205
What do you mean by that?

369
00:26:52,205 --> 00:26:53,538
My daughter is dead?

370
00:26:53,538 --> 00:26:55,113
Did they

371
00:26:55,113 --> 00:26:57,338
at least find her body?

372
00:26:58,038 --> 00:26:59,705
No.

373
00:26:59,705 --> 00:27:01,929
But it's certain

374
00:27:01,929 --> 00:27:03,038
that Hye Jin is dead.

375
00:27:03,038 --> 00:27:05,605
How can you be so sure?

376
00:27:05,605 --> 00:27:07,538
Have you even seen my daughter's body?

377
00:27:07,538 --> 00:27:10,138
We received a tip from someone claiming
they'd seen Hye Jin's body.

378
00:27:10,138 --> 00:27:12,472
Who was that?

379
00:27:14,072 --> 00:27:15,705
Well, that's...

380
00:27:17,805 --> 00:27:19,405
A tip...

381
00:27:20,372 --> 00:27:23,505
What if the tip was just a prank?

382
00:27:24,305 --> 00:27:27,472
Give up hope that Hye Jin will come back.

383
00:27:28,438 --> 00:27:30,672
And stop looking for her.

384
00:27:31,905 --> 00:27:33,705
Just

385
00:27:33,705 --> 00:27:36,138
pretend she's dead and go on with your life.

386
00:27:38,572 --> 00:27:39,938
Get out right now!

387
00:27:39,938 --> 00:27:42,105
Don't ever come near this house again!

388
00:27:42,105 --> 00:27:44,372
Do you understand me?

389
00:27:52,438 --> 00:27:55,172
Hye Jin...

390
00:28:00,238 --> 00:28:05,372
My wife went out looking for her
even the day before she died.

391
00:28:06,438 --> 00:28:10,838
She was barely living at all.

392
00:28:12,438 --> 00:28:15,972
Even alive, she looked dead inside.

393
00:28:18,729 --> 00:28:21,833
[Searching for the Missing]

394
00:28:28,538 --> 00:28:29,668
That...

395
00:28:30,281 --> 00:28:32,265
That killer...

396
00:28:32,265 --> 00:28:36,472
Could I meet him?

397
00:28:39,338 --> 00:28:41,105
You mean Lee Yong Woo?

398
00:28:42,538 --> 00:28:45,097
[Victim of Kangseng Murder Case]
So we're thinking of assembling

399
00:28:45,097 --> 00:28:46,672
a special reporting team.

400
00:28:46,672 --> 00:28:49,538
How many people can be assigned right away?

401
00:28:49,538 --> 00:28:54,057
At the moment, maybe three or four people?

402
00:28:54,057 --> 00:28:56,425
It's the profile of Kangseng Serial Killer

403
00:28:56,425 --> 00:28:58,638
- Lee Yong Woo.
- Oh.

404
00:29:10,205 --> 00:29:12,705
Ma'am?

405
00:29:12,705 --> 00:29:14,372
What's wrong?

406
00:29:16,238 --> 00:29:18,505
Do you know him?

407
00:29:18,505 --> 00:29:20,872
Wait, how would she know Lee Yong Woo?

408
00:29:20,872 --> 00:29:24,905
The director's from Kangseng.

409
00:29:24,905 --> 00:29:26,205
Keep going with the report.

410
00:29:26,205 --> 00:29:28,972
Yes, and Profiler Kang Tae Joo

411
00:29:28,972 --> 00:29:31,805
is currently in full charge
of the meetings with Lee Yong Woo.

412
00:29:32,505 --> 00:29:34,172
Did Professor Kang Tae Joo volunteer for it?

413
00:29:34,172 --> 00:29:35,238
No.

414
00:29:35,238 --> 00:29:40,172
According to rumors, Lee Yong Woo
specifically requested him.

415
00:29:41,338 --> 00:29:42,805
Lee Yong Woo himself?

416
00:29:42,805 --> 00:29:44,505
Yes.

417
00:29:44,505 --> 00:29:45,805
And nobody knows why?

418
00:29:45,805 --> 00:29:47,405
No.

419
00:29:48,505 --> 00:29:50,972
<i>What on earth were you thinking?</i>

420
00:30:15,372 --> 00:30:17,572
That was you too?

421
00:30:31,638 --> 00:30:35,172
What's wrong? Are you not feeling well?

422
00:30:41,172 --> 00:30:44,405
I can't listen to this.

423
00:30:44,405 --> 00:30:46,172
That monster

424
00:30:46,172 --> 00:30:48,738
talking about killing my daughter.

425
00:30:50,238 --> 00:30:52,372
I can't bear to hear it.

426
00:30:54,672 --> 00:30:57,038
Alright, then,

427
00:30:57,038 --> 00:30:59,172
I'll go instead.

428
00:30:59,172 --> 00:31:01,138
Father, stay here. Okay?

429
00:31:01,138 --> 00:31:02,172
I'll...

430
00:31:02,172 --> 00:31:05,605
Please take good care of my father.

431
00:31:06,338 --> 00:31:08,272
Go on then.

432
00:31:14,905 --> 00:31:20,505
[Musan Prison]

433
00:31:25,105 --> 00:31:27,881
Professor Kang

434
00:31:27,881 --> 00:31:30,105
told me about you.

435
00:31:30,105 --> 00:31:32,538
That you're the girl's family.

436
00:31:37,005 --> 00:31:39,272
Back when my sister went missing,

437
00:31:41,838 --> 00:31:45,272
I was just six years old.

438
00:31:45,272 --> 00:31:47,538
But I remember.

439
00:31:48,238 --> 00:31:51,438
In our house, once filled with laughter,

440
00:31:51,438 --> 00:31:54,472
no one ever laughed again.

441
00:31:57,238 --> 00:32:00,405
Why my sister of all people?

442
00:32:00,405 --> 00:32:02,238
Why my sister?

443
00:32:06,938 --> 00:32:08,572
I...

444
00:32:09,338 --> 00:32:11,338
feel sorry too.

445
00:32:12,305 --> 00:32:14,372
That day,

446
00:32:14,372 --> 00:32:16,205
at that exact moment,

447
00:32:18,138 --> 00:32:21,138
she just happened to pass by there.

448
00:32:22,638 --> 00:32:26,305
She was simply unlucky.

449
00:32:31,305 --> 00:32:32,905
That is...

450
00:32:34,238 --> 00:32:36,638
that is all?

451
00:32:36,638 --> 00:32:38,238
Oh, dear.

452
00:32:39,872 --> 00:32:41,805
Anyway,

453
00:32:41,805 --> 00:32:44,638
I truly feel sorry about it.

454
00:33:06,872 --> 00:33:08,638
Oh,

455
00:33:08,638 --> 00:33:10,272
Professor!

456
00:33:15,438 --> 00:33:17,138
Mr. Cha.

457
00:33:21,572 --> 00:33:24,138
- Here you go.
- Oh, thank you.

458
00:33:25,805 --> 00:33:27,605
Sorry for dropping by so suddenly.

459
00:33:27,605 --> 00:33:28,805
Not at all.

460
00:33:28,805 --> 00:33:31,405
I wasn't actually planning to see you today.

461
00:33:31,405 --> 00:33:33,938
But I was just going to leave
a message with your assistant.

462
00:33:33,938 --> 00:33:35,572
That's alright.

463
00:33:40,438 --> 00:33:44,672
But what brings you here?

464
00:33:45,505 --> 00:33:48,538
While investigating Mr. Im Seok Man's case,

465
00:33:49,438 --> 00:33:52,572
I came across something
called a radioactive isotope test.

466
00:33:54,038 --> 00:33:56,772
And it turns out you submitted it, Professor.

467
00:33:57,405 --> 00:34:00,772
[Radioisotope Analysis Report]

468
00:34:00,772 --> 00:34:04,638
Back then, forensic science
barely even existed as a concept.

469
00:34:04,638 --> 00:34:07,705
At most, we could identify blood types.

470
00:34:07,705 --> 00:34:12,238
So honestly, I was fascinated
by that test at the time.

471
00:34:12,972 --> 00:34:16,305
So are you saying
you no longer trust the test?

472
00:34:16,305 --> 00:34:17,938
Of course not.

473
00:34:19,338 --> 00:34:22,705
That test was used as evidence in court,

474
00:34:23,972 --> 00:34:26,105
so I bear significant responsibility.

475
00:34:32,638 --> 00:34:33,878
You look

476
00:34:33,878 --> 00:34:36,505
disappointed in me.

477
00:34:36,505 --> 00:34:38,705
No.

478
00:34:38,705 --> 00:34:42,057
I'm impressed by how honest you are

479
00:34:42,057 --> 00:34:43,738
acknowledging your mistakes.

480
00:34:46,172 --> 00:34:47,938
It's only right.

481
00:34:50,038 --> 00:34:54,838
Did the prosecutor in charge also
know the evidence was unreliable?

482
00:34:58,038 --> 00:34:59,638
Hard to say.

483
00:35:01,138 --> 00:35:03,772
Even if he did, it wouldn't have been

484
00:35:03,772 --> 00:35:06,405
easy for him to admit it.

485
00:35:10,038 --> 00:35:11,638
I see.

486
00:35:20,705 --> 00:35:22,305
Thank you for taking the time
to meet with me today.

487
00:35:22,305 --> 00:35:24,238
Oh, no need to thank me.

488
00:35:24,238 --> 00:35:26,338
Have you eaten? Or...

489
00:35:26,338 --> 00:35:30,238
Yes, I had another appointment,
so I ate beforehand.

490
00:35:31,472 --> 00:35:34,038
Make sure you eat properly.

491
00:35:34,038 --> 00:35:36,305
Don't skip meals.

492
00:35:36,305 --> 00:35:38,538
You sound just like my uncle.

493
00:35:40,172 --> 00:35:44,972
Every time he sees me, the first thing
he asks is whether I've eaten.

494
00:35:50,238 --> 00:35:55,838
[Gyeonggi Eastern Police Agency]

495
00:35:58,105 --> 00:35:59,905
Good work.

496
00:36:01,638 --> 00:36:04,472
I'm here to see Commissioner Park Dae Ho.

497
00:36:04,472 --> 00:36:07,272
Did you make an appointment?

498
00:36:07,272 --> 00:36:08,338
No.

499
00:36:08,338 --> 00:36:11,572
Then how may I address you?

500
00:36:11,572 --> 00:36:14,805
Just tell him it's Kang Tae Joo. He'll know.

501
00:36:16,172 --> 00:36:17,838
One moment, please.

502
00:36:19,972 --> 00:36:21,572
Who?

503
00:36:22,738 --> 00:36:24,872
Oh, Kang Tae Joo?

504
00:36:25,738 --> 00:36:29,038
Tell him to wait since I have guests.

505
00:36:39,372 --> 00:36:44,238
I'll handle it, so you don't end up
in trouble, Assemblyman Cha.

506
00:36:47,305 --> 00:36:49,238
I know very well

507
00:36:49,238 --> 00:36:53,505
how cleanly you handle things.

508
00:37:01,972 --> 00:37:03,305
Try some of this too.

509
00:37:03,305 --> 00:37:05,438
Why do you keep giving me food?

510
00:37:05,438 --> 00:37:06,972
I can't finish all this.

511
00:37:06,972 --> 00:37:10,205
Thanks to you, Dae Ho
got a special promotion, sir.

512
00:37:10,205 --> 00:37:11,905
It wasn't because of me.

513
00:37:11,905 --> 00:37:14,538
Detective Park Dae Ho earned it himself.

514
00:37:15,572 --> 00:37:20,705
Detective Park will do great things
and be a good son to you.

515
00:37:22,638 --> 00:37:25,438
Oh, just hearing that makes me happy.

516
00:37:26,338 --> 00:37:28,572
Then enjoy your meal.

517
00:37:28,572 --> 00:37:30,305
Thank you for the meal.

518
00:37:32,738 --> 00:37:36,638
Your mother really worries about you.

519
00:37:36,638 --> 00:37:39,005
What brings you to my house?

520
00:37:39,005 --> 00:37:41,172
Detective Park, you're good at everything,

521
00:37:42,972 --> 00:37:45,272
except your mouth is too loose.

522
00:37:47,538 --> 00:37:50,772
You told Kang Tae Joo
something you never should have.

523
00:37:56,605 --> 00:37:58,538
I'm going to turn myself in.

524
00:38:00,105 --> 00:38:01,738
Then do it.

525
00:38:03,138 --> 00:38:05,805
But you take full responsibility alone.

526
00:38:05,805 --> 00:38:07,972
What are you talking about?

527
00:38:10,872 --> 00:38:13,738
You gave the order, Prosecutor Cha.

528
00:38:19,872 --> 00:38:21,225
If I,

529
00:38:21,225 --> 00:38:23,305
Detective Jang, and Detective Do

530
00:38:23,305 --> 00:38:26,038
all get our stories straight,

531
00:38:26,038 --> 00:38:28,238
which version becomes the truth?

532
00:38:33,305 --> 00:38:34,838
It's only your mother I feel sorry for.

533
00:38:34,838 --> 00:38:36,772
She's so happy

534
00:38:39,705 --> 00:38:42,005
you got promoted.

535
00:38:42,005 --> 00:38:44,472
Not knowing you'll be in handcuffs soon.

536
00:38:46,472 --> 00:38:49,005
Think about only one thing,

537
00:38:49,005 --> 00:38:51,472
what's truly best for your mother.

538
00:39:05,338 --> 00:39:06,972
Dae Ho,

539
00:39:07,805 --> 00:39:11,438
help me find Hye Jin by telling the truth.

540
00:39:11,438 --> 00:39:14,838
If you say Cha Si Young ordered it,
you might get some leniency.

541
00:39:14,838 --> 00:39:17,805
I don't know what you're talking about.

542
00:39:19,138 --> 00:39:20,372
What's wrong with you?

543
00:39:20,372 --> 00:39:23,205
Were you threatened or something?

544
00:39:23,205 --> 00:39:24,505
Is that it?

545
00:39:24,505 --> 00:39:27,572
I only get threatened
if I've done something wrong.

546
00:39:27,572 --> 00:39:29,438
What did I even do?

547
00:39:30,238 --> 00:39:31,238
Dae Ho!

548
00:39:31,238 --> 00:39:33,872
If we cover this up,
what about Hye Jin's family?

549
00:39:33,872 --> 00:39:34,972
Huh?

550
00:39:34,972 --> 00:39:35,972
You saw it yourself.

551
00:39:35,972 --> 00:39:41,205
Hye Jin's parents will keep searching
all their lives, not knowing she's dead.

552
00:39:41,205 --> 00:39:44,705
Can you really live on
pretending you don't know that?

553
00:39:44,705 --> 00:39:47,405
I told you.

554
00:39:47,405 --> 00:39:50,038
I don't know what you're talking about.

555
00:40:03,272 --> 00:40:06,938
I didn't know you
and Cha Si Young were that close.

556
00:40:08,105 --> 00:40:11,172
I wouldn't say we were that close,

557
00:40:11,172 --> 00:40:15,705
but it's true our connection didn't end
and has continued on.

558
00:40:17,072 --> 00:40:21,405
Then you must've already known why I came.

559
00:40:23,172 --> 00:40:25,805
I met Hye Jin's father.

560
00:40:27,238 --> 00:40:29,905
Her mother has already passed away,

561
00:40:32,438 --> 00:40:35,038
and her father begged me.

562
00:40:35,038 --> 00:40:38,938
He asked me to at least
help him find her body.

563
00:40:40,238 --> 00:40:42,772
Right, back then,

564
00:40:42,772 --> 00:40:46,238
you probably had no choice.

565
00:40:46,238 --> 00:40:49,638
Right, you were probably under threat.

566
00:40:49,638 --> 00:40:52,672
But things have changed now.

567
00:40:52,672 --> 00:40:56,872
You're not just a sergeant.
You're the Police Commissioner now.

568
00:40:58,772 --> 00:41:00,438
Even if it's late,

569
00:41:01,472 --> 00:41:04,605
can't you finally tell the truth

570
00:41:04,605 --> 00:41:07,338
to Hye Jin's family?

571
00:41:15,005 --> 00:41:16,705
Dae Ho!

572
00:41:18,638 --> 00:41:20,272
Oh, dear.

573
00:41:21,805 --> 00:41:24,605
You haven't changed a bit, sir.

574
00:41:31,938 --> 00:41:35,405
The young Park Dae Ho I knew

575
00:41:35,405 --> 00:41:39,472
was a curious man
with a strong sense of justice.

576
00:41:40,105 --> 00:41:42,105
He always had a willingness to learn.

577
00:41:42,105 --> 00:41:44,038
Sir,

578
00:41:44,038 --> 00:41:47,905
what exactly are you trying to say to me?

579
00:41:49,805 --> 00:41:51,972
What if

580
00:41:53,405 --> 00:41:58,105
you had started your police career somewhere
other than Kangseng back then?

581
00:41:58,105 --> 00:42:00,038
How would things be?

582
00:42:02,105 --> 00:42:03,805
That...

583
00:42:05,505 --> 00:42:07,772
is something I really regret,
and I'm sorry to you.

584
00:42:17,005 --> 00:42:18,089
What?

585
00:42:18,761 --> 00:42:21,338
Kang Tae Joo came to see you?

586
00:42:21,338 --> 00:42:23,772
He even came to my company.

587
00:42:25,038 --> 00:42:30,272
That punk must still think
I'm the Park Sang Beom from 30 years ago.

588
00:42:30,272 --> 00:42:34,072
There are apartment complexes
in Korea named after me.

589
00:42:35,205 --> 00:42:37,572
How dare he come so boldly!

590
00:42:37,572 --> 00:42:39,672
So what exactly did he say?

591
00:42:41,372 --> 00:42:43,049
Well,

592
00:42:43,049 --> 00:42:45,805
he said the statute of limitations expired,

593
00:42:45,805 --> 00:42:47,605
so no one would be punished.

594
00:42:47,605 --> 00:42:51,005
So he told me to admit everything in court

595
00:42:51,005 --> 00:42:53,038
and properly apologize.

596
00:42:56,072 --> 00:42:57,705
Jeez.

597
00:42:58,538 --> 00:43:00,838
That's so like Kang Tae Joo.

598
00:43:01,938 --> 00:43:06,638
He wastes his sincerity on pointless things.

599
00:43:08,338 --> 00:43:11,593
I should've buried that punk back then.

600
00:43:11,593 --> 00:43:14,438
Why did you let him live?
That's not like you.

601
00:43:18,938 --> 00:43:20,972
Are you just going to leave him be?

602
00:43:25,172 --> 00:43:26,805
Let him be.

603
00:43:27,972 --> 00:43:31,538
The statute of limitations has passed anyway.

604
00:43:31,538 --> 00:43:35,538
He's just doing pointless things
because he can't do anything about it.

605
00:43:35,538 --> 00:43:37,605
Just to feel better himself.

606
00:43:38,972 --> 00:43:43,238
Well, you always make exceptions for him.

607
00:43:43,238 --> 00:43:47,438
You act like you despise him,
but it doesn't seem like that's all there is.

608
00:43:47,438 --> 00:43:50,438
But it's not like that you like him, either.

609
00:43:54,772 --> 00:43:57,938
It must be because of
Sun Young and Young Beom.

610
00:43:58,972 --> 00:44:02,805
No, it's been like that much longer

611
00:44:02,805 --> 00:44:05,005
since our school days.

612
00:44:17,905 --> 00:44:23,272
So everyone is just pretending not to know?

613
00:44:23,938 --> 00:44:26,372
That's what I'm saying.

614
00:44:28,305 --> 00:44:31,338
Doesn't it feel like
everything's been reversed?

615
00:44:31,338 --> 00:44:37,038
Even I, a murderer, am telling the truth,
while the police are the ones lying.

616
00:44:47,705 --> 00:44:49,305
Ki Hwan.

617
00:44:49,305 --> 00:44:50,889
Could you testify

618
00:44:50,889 --> 00:44:54,638
as a witness for Seok Man's trial?

619
00:44:58,038 --> 00:44:59,272
Why would I?

620
00:44:59,272 --> 00:45:02,538
You're the only one who can prove

621
00:45:03,405 --> 00:45:05,038
Seok Man's innocence now.

622
00:45:10,238 --> 00:45:12,605
Come on, that's a bit...

623
00:45:14,072 --> 00:45:17,672
I think I've done enough already.

624
00:45:17,672 --> 00:45:19,505
12 plus 2.

625
00:45:19,505 --> 00:45:24,305
The reason you separated
the Im Seok Man and Yoon Hye Jin cases.

626
00:45:24,305 --> 00:45:27,205
Yes, those twelve are entirely your crimes,

627
00:45:27,205 --> 00:45:29,472
but the remaining two

628
00:45:29,472 --> 00:45:32,705
involved other perpetrators besides you.

629
00:45:32,705 --> 00:45:37,572
Don't you think those other perpetrators
should be punished too?

630
00:45:39,272 --> 00:45:41,005
Exactly.

631
00:45:42,738 --> 00:45:45,972
I'm not just trying to prove
Im Seok Man's innocence.

632
00:45:47,338 --> 00:45:49,738
I want to expose

633
00:45:49,738 --> 00:45:52,972
everything the prosecutors and police did

634
00:45:54,038 --> 00:45:57,605
to Seok Man, Hye Jin,

635
00:46:00,338 --> 00:46:02,138
and their families.

636
00:46:15,905 --> 00:46:17,605
But,

637
00:46:20,605 --> 00:46:23,538
that's your job, not mine.

638
00:46:24,705 --> 00:46:27,405
Figure it out yourself, my friend.

639
00:46:28,372 --> 00:46:32,605
If Lee Yong Woo doesn't testify
as a witness, it'll favor the prosecution.

640
00:46:33,372 --> 00:46:36,305
[Attorney Cha Yeon Ho's Office]
That's exactly what the perpetrators want.

641
00:46:36,305 --> 00:46:40,205
And the prosecutors used to work
under Assemblyman Cha for a long time.

642
00:46:40,205 --> 00:46:43,505
Then the trial will go exactly
as Cha Si Young intends.

643
00:46:43,505 --> 00:46:46,338
What kind of strategy are they planning?

644
00:46:49,538 --> 00:46:51,705
Well,

645
00:46:51,705 --> 00:46:55,772
there will be a retrial for Im Seok Man soon.

646
00:46:57,438 --> 00:46:59,369
All of us

647
00:46:59,369 --> 00:47:01,872
could end up being called as witnesses.

648
00:47:02,638 --> 00:47:06,505
Are you saying he could be acquitted now?

649
00:47:06,505 --> 00:47:10,372
It doesn't matter. The statute of limitations
has already passed anyway.

650
00:47:10,372 --> 00:47:14,438
Still, won't there be public backlash?

651
00:47:14,438 --> 00:47:18,805
Especially, since you're
a public figure, Assemblyman.

652
00:47:18,805 --> 00:47:22,605
If only that punk Lee Yong Woo
hadn't made that statement.

653
00:47:24,905 --> 00:47:29,438
What troubles them most right now
is the real killer's confession.

654
00:47:29,438 --> 00:47:31,872
They will want to deny it somehow.

655
00:47:32,605 --> 00:47:34,505
Is there any way they can deny it?

656
00:47:34,505 --> 00:47:38,305
That would mean Lee Yong Woo lied.

657
00:47:38,305 --> 00:47:40,138
Lied?

658
00:47:43,538 --> 00:47:45,605
Serial killer Yoo Cheol Young.

659
00:47:45,605 --> 00:47:49,838
Do you happen to remember
serial killer Yoo Cheol Young?

660
00:47:49,838 --> 00:47:51,372
Yoo Cheol Young?

661
00:47:51,372 --> 00:47:54,505
In fact, Yoo Cheol Young
even confessed to crimes

662
00:47:54,505 --> 00:47:58,505
committed by another serial killer
to exaggerate his own.

663
00:47:58,505 --> 00:48:00,538
It was all driven
by his desire for attention.

664
00:48:00,538 --> 00:48:04,438
So we dismiss Lee Yong Woo's confession
as an act for attention?

665
00:48:04,438 --> 00:48:06,205
Yes.

666
00:48:06,838 --> 00:48:09,605
It's already been 30 years.

667
00:48:09,605 --> 00:48:13,905
How much could he possibly remember
after all this time?

668
00:48:21,072 --> 00:48:23,305
I'll call the prosecutor in charge.

669
00:48:23,305 --> 00:48:24,938
Okay.

670
00:48:27,205 --> 00:48:31,405
If the prosecutor raises issues
without Lee Yong Woo present,

671
00:48:31,405 --> 00:48:33,538
it could work against the verdict.

672
00:48:34,172 --> 00:48:38,438
Attorney Cha, when is Lee Yong Woo
scheduled for prosecution summons?

673
00:48:39,505 --> 00:48:41,272
Today.

674
00:48:44,172 --> 00:48:45,805
Maybe

675
00:48:46,638 --> 00:48:48,938
there is a way after all.

676
00:48:59,305 --> 00:49:02,972
[Prosecutors' Office Annex]

677
00:49:02,972 --> 00:49:06,272
[Suspect Interrogation Record]

678
00:49:32,872 --> 00:49:37,105
Are you saying you also committed
the 7th case, Mr. Lee Yong Woo?

679
00:49:37,105 --> 00:49:38,838
Yes.

680
00:49:40,649 --> 00:49:42,205
Oh, my.

681
00:49:42,205 --> 00:49:45,438
Stockings look great on you.

682
00:49:52,172 --> 00:49:55,805
Can you prove that?

683
00:49:57,038 --> 00:49:59,638
Well, they're right in front of me.

684
00:49:59,638 --> 00:50:01,472
No,

685
00:50:01,472 --> 00:50:05,372
I mean the 7th case.

686
00:50:08,438 --> 00:50:09,772
Wow.

687
00:50:09,772 --> 00:50:14,472
Do I have to both confess
and prove it myself?

688
00:50:15,238 --> 00:50:18,505
Everyone knows you're
obsessed with stockings.

689
00:50:18,505 --> 00:50:20,938
But why was the 7th case the only one

690
00:50:20,938 --> 00:50:25,193
involving a sleeping child
instead of stockings?

691
00:50:25,193 --> 00:50:28,838
That's random and suspicious.

692
00:50:28,838 --> 00:50:31,372
What, are you saying I'm lying right now?

693
00:50:31,372 --> 00:50:32,972
Lee Yong Woo.

694
00:50:33,772 --> 00:50:38,838
It seems like you've always been cheered on
whenever you open your mouth.

695
00:50:38,838 --> 00:50:40,672
But this place is different.

696
00:50:40,672 --> 00:50:45,205
This isn't a place where we blindly believe
whatever criminals say.

697
00:50:53,838 --> 00:50:55,438
Why would I lie?

698
00:50:57,172 --> 00:51:00,272
Why would I confess to something I didn't do?

699
00:51:04,472 --> 00:51:08,538
Don't serial killers do that kind of thing?

700
00:51:08,538 --> 00:51:11,538
Competing over who killed more,

701
00:51:13,005 --> 00:51:16,705
ranking themselves like it's a contest.

702
00:51:46,705 --> 00:51:49,872
[The Truth of the 1988
Kangseng Yoon Hye Jin Case]

703
00:51:49,872 --> 00:51:52,972
"scarecrow1988."

704
00:51:54,905 --> 00:51:56,238
Scarecrow...

705
00:51:56,238 --> 00:52:00,305
[The Truth of the 1988
Kangseng Yoon Hye Jin Case]

706
00:52:00,305 --> 00:52:01,938
[Yoon Hye Jin Case File,
Yoon Hye Jin 2019 Missing Person Flyer]

707
00:52:01,938 --> 00:52:05,513
[Estimated Current Appearance]

708
00:52:13,972 --> 00:52:17,338
[Searching for the Missing]

709
00:52:21,338 --> 00:52:23,972
There's nothing more I can do.

710
00:52:23,972 --> 00:52:26,672
I don't even know
who's the scarecrow anymore.

711
00:52:44,738 --> 00:52:46,738
What a fool...

712
00:52:48,272 --> 00:52:50,938
How did he carry

713
00:52:53,638 --> 00:52:57,605
something so heavy alone for 30 years?

714
00:53:17,872 --> 00:53:21,105
- You're Mr. Im Seok Man, correct?
- Oh my, you startled me!

715
00:53:21,105 --> 00:53:25,538
Hello! I'm Cha Young Beom,
a reporter from Noise Cut.

716
00:53:30,872 --> 00:53:33,605
Oh, I surprised you, didn't I?
Coming by so suddenly like this.

717
00:53:33,605 --> 00:53:38,605
I always drop by during the day, but you were
never around, so I came early this morning.

718
00:53:38,605 --> 00:53:40,405
Luckily, you're here.

719
00:53:42,038 --> 00:53:43,638
Ki Beom...

720
00:53:45,872 --> 00:53:49,305
Do you know my father?

721
00:54:04,505 --> 00:54:06,938
Wow.

722
00:54:06,938 --> 00:54:09,272
This is the first time
I've seen a photo of my father.

723
00:54:09,272 --> 00:54:11,405
Your father is handsome, isn't he?

724
00:54:11,405 --> 00:54:14,405
Good-looking and kind.

725
00:54:16,338 --> 00:54:18,738
If only that incident hadn't happened...

726
00:54:20,272 --> 00:54:25,672
I was also a victim of abuse, but it doesn't
compare to your father who lost his life.

727
00:54:28,205 --> 00:54:31,305
What do you mean?

728
00:54:33,172 --> 00:54:35,038
My father

729
00:54:35,738 --> 00:54:38,605
was a victim of abuse?

730
00:54:38,605 --> 00:54:41,805
I know there's been a lot of criticism
about the policies

731
00:54:41,805 --> 00:54:43,172
we've put forward.

732
00:54:43,172 --> 00:54:48,205
But if noise like this starts already,
what are we supposed to do?

733
00:54:49,005 --> 00:54:51,005
He's in a meeting right now.

734
00:54:55,072 --> 00:54:57,172
Shall we take a short break?

735
00:55:06,538 --> 00:55:09,305
What? What's going on?

736
00:55:09,305 --> 00:55:10,938
My father

737
00:55:11,638 --> 00:55:13,972
didn't die in a traffic accident, did he?

738
00:55:16,681 --> 00:55:18,073
Jeez.

739
00:55:18,938 --> 00:55:23,238
I don't know where you heard that from...

740
00:55:23,238 --> 00:55:26,338
Is it true he died
after being tortured by the police?

741
00:55:33,138 --> 00:55:35,605
[Suspect dies due to police brutality.
Disciplinary action against Mr. Kang]

742
00:55:35,605 --> 00:55:37,405
[Measures for Dismissed Public Officials]

743
00:55:40,938 --> 00:55:42,572
[Suspect dies due to police brutality.
Disciplinary action against Mr. Kang]

744
00:55:42,572 --> 00:55:45,338
You know who this Mr. Kang is,

745
00:55:46,372 --> 00:55:48,138
right, Uncle?

746
00:55:51,072 --> 00:55:54,205
It's all in the past.

747
00:55:54,205 --> 00:55:56,172
No,

748
00:55:56,172 --> 00:55:58,005
I need to know.

749
00:56:02,438 --> 00:56:04,972
I'm not exactly going to do
anything about it at this point.

750
00:56:04,972 --> 00:56:07,305
I only want to find out the truth.

751
00:56:08,005 --> 00:56:10,738
I have the right to know. After all...

752
00:56:12,772 --> 00:56:14,638
I am his son.

753
00:56:16,872 --> 00:56:18,572
So tell me.

754
00:56:20,272 --> 00:56:22,605
Just the name of the sergeant
who caused my father's death.

755
00:56:28,238 --> 00:56:32,205
[Suspect dies due to police brutality.
Disciplinary action against Mr. Kang]

756
00:56:36,438 --> 00:56:38,172
Kang Tae Joo.

757
00:56:41,105 --> 00:56:42,105
What?

758
00:56:42,105 --> 00:56:45,172
The Mr. Kang mentioned here

759
00:56:45,172 --> 00:56:47,272
is Kang Tae Joo.

760
00:56:59,805 --> 00:57:02,272
Make sure you eat properly.

761
00:57:02,272 --> 00:57:04,305
Don't skip meals.

762
00:57:08,841 --> 00:57:09,929
[Record of calls]

763
00:57:18,633 --> 00:57:20,572
It's me.

764
00:57:20,572 --> 00:57:22,705
Young Beom came and left.

765
00:57:24,938 --> 00:57:27,905
He was asking about his father's death.

766
00:58:08,372 --> 00:58:10,038
Sun Young!

767
00:58:23,538 --> 00:58:26,238
It's really been a long time,

768
00:58:26,938 --> 00:58:28,538
hasn't it?

769
00:58:30,953 --> 00:58:32,473
Yeah.

770
00:58:39,305 --> 00:58:41,405
Assemblyman Cha Mu Jin.

771
00:58:42,205 --> 00:58:45,005
I heard the news of his passing.

772
00:58:45,005 --> 00:58:49,805
He was strict, but he cared about me a lot.

773
00:58:49,805 --> 00:58:52,038
I don't regret

774
00:58:52,772 --> 00:58:54,772
living as his daughter.

775
00:58:55,538 --> 00:58:57,505
Well, I'm glad to hear that.

776
00:58:58,438 --> 00:59:02,938
I met Young Beom a few days ago.

777
00:59:02,938 --> 00:59:05,172
He came for an interview with me.

778
00:59:05,172 --> 00:59:06,905
Young Beom?

779
00:59:07,638 --> 00:59:10,605
Don't worry. I didn't tell him much.

780
00:59:13,905 --> 00:59:15,505
Tae Joo.

781
00:59:16,305 --> 00:59:18,572
I'm not a good mother.

782
00:59:19,438 --> 00:59:22,672
I wasn't a good mother to him.

783
00:59:22,672 --> 00:59:24,672
Before giving birth,

784
00:59:26,172 --> 00:59:30,038
I had an accident, a traffic accident.

785
00:59:30,038 --> 00:59:35,505
I gave birth to Young Beom while in a coma,
and woke up six months later.

786
00:59:35,505 --> 00:59:39,705
<i>Then I spent another
six months in rehabilitation.</i>

787
00:59:39,705 --> 00:59:41,605
<i>And when I finally went home...</i>

788
00:59:41,605 --> 00:59:44,005
We're going out to play. Oh, no!

789
00:59:44,638 --> 00:59:46,838
It hurts. Don't do that!

790
00:59:46,838 --> 00:59:50,638
Oh no, please stop. It hurts!

791
00:59:50,638 --> 00:59:52,238
Then...

792
00:59:55,238 --> 00:59:57,138
Young Beom!

793
00:59:58,238 --> 01:00:00,772
Young Beom, Mommy's here.

794
01:00:00,772 --> 01:00:02,672
- Mommy's here.
- Young Beom, it's Mommy.

795
01:00:02,672 --> 01:00:06,105
Mommy's here. Let's go to Mommy.

796
01:00:06,105 --> 01:00:07,872
Shall we go to Mommy?

797
01:00:07,872 --> 01:00:09,472
Come here!

798
01:00:20,938 --> 01:00:25,272
Oh dear, why are you crying?

799
01:00:25,272 --> 01:00:27,672
But you missed your mommy.

800
01:00:28,605 --> 01:00:30,205
Alright.

801
01:00:32,205 --> 01:00:35,172
Don't cry, alright.

802
01:00:35,172 --> 01:00:38,472
<i>I could hardly bear to watch the two of them</i>

803
01:00:40,038 --> 01:00:42,505
<i>being so close like father and son.</i>

804
01:00:43,672 --> 01:00:46,538
<i>Young Beom didn't feel like my son.</i>

805
01:00:48,038 --> 01:00:50,305
Even now, Young Beom

806
01:00:50,305 --> 01:00:53,205
follows his uncle more than he follows me.

807
01:00:54,572 --> 01:00:58,438
Like it or not, that man Cha Si Young

808
01:00:58,438 --> 01:01:00,372
is like a father

809
01:01:01,138 --> 01:01:03,405
to Young Beom.

810
01:01:10,505 --> 01:01:13,472
The reason I asked to meet you today is

811
01:01:14,272 --> 01:01:18,638
it seems Young Beom has found out
about his father's death.

812
01:01:18,638 --> 01:01:23,138
He believes the officer who tortured Ki Beom

813
01:01:23,138 --> 01:01:25,638
was you.

814
01:01:28,872 --> 01:01:30,505
So...

815
01:01:36,672 --> 01:01:38,805
just let him think it was you.

816
01:01:40,072 --> 01:01:42,905
If he finds out that the uncle
he looks up to like a father

817
01:01:44,538 --> 01:01:46,905
caused his own father's death,

818
01:01:47,938 --> 01:01:50,838
he won't be able to handle it.

819
01:01:51,638 --> 01:01:53,272
So,

820
01:01:54,372 --> 01:01:56,472
please help me, Tae Joo.

821
01:02:00,705 --> 01:02:02,338
Alright.

822
01:02:04,305 --> 01:02:05,938
I will.

823
01:02:12,238 --> 01:02:13,838
Thank you.

824
01:02:15,472 --> 01:02:17,138
Thank you?

825
01:02:17,838 --> 01:02:20,138
Don't mention it. You're Young Beom's mother.

826
01:02:20,138 --> 01:02:22,272
You should take care of him.

827
01:02:24,605 --> 01:02:28,272
And no matter how much he likes his uncle,

828
01:02:28,272 --> 01:02:30,772
how could he ever replace his mother?

829
01:02:30,772 --> 01:02:32,372
Don't you think?

830
01:03:42,538 --> 01:03:44,905
Do you remember Lee Ki Beom?

831
01:03:48,338 --> 01:03:51,438
He was a suspect
in the Kangseng Serial Murder Case.

832
01:03:51,438 --> 01:03:55,838
He died while in custody
during police interrogation.

833
01:03:55,838 --> 01:03:58,238
Aren't you curious
why I brought up Lee Ki Beom?

834
01:03:58,238 --> 01:04:00,805
He was your father, wasn't he, Mr. Cha?

835
01:04:00,805 --> 01:04:02,572
Lee Ki Beom.

836
01:04:04,838 --> 01:04:06,938
Did you already know?

837
01:04:07,838 --> 01:04:09,905
Because you look just like him.

838
01:04:10,672 --> 01:04:12,305
How could you...

839
01:04:13,405 --> 01:04:16,905
How could you do that
when you know full well?

840
01:04:16,905 --> 01:04:19,872
How could you laugh
and talk with me like that?

841
01:04:21,805 --> 01:04:24,338
Did you really do it, Professor?

842
01:04:25,505 --> 01:04:28,838
Are you really the one who killed my father?

843
01:04:31,805 --> 01:04:33,438
Yes.

844
01:04:35,972 --> 01:04:37,638
I'm sorry.

845
01:04:40,138 --> 01:04:42,372
No matter what the times were like,

846
01:04:42,372 --> 01:04:45,038
how could you beat someone to death?

847
01:04:45,972 --> 01:04:48,072
A human being shouldn't
do something like that!

848
01:04:48,072 --> 01:04:50,538
How can a human do that to another human?

849
01:04:53,972 --> 01:04:56,705
I never knew why I was drawn

850
01:04:57,372 --> 01:04:59,805
to this case until now.

851
01:05:00,738 --> 01:05:02,738
But now I understand.

852
01:05:03,638 --> 01:05:05,972
That I've been given a purpose.

853
01:05:08,038 --> 01:05:10,005
I won't stand by

854
01:05:10,005 --> 01:05:13,338
and watch people be deceived by you.

855
01:05:57,405 --> 01:05:59,605
Going live in 10 seconds!

856
01:05:59,605 --> 01:06:02,672
An exclusive interview
with a murderer, Noise Cut report.

857
01:06:02,672 --> 01:06:05,605
So a murderer has exposed
the truth the police buried.

858
01:06:05,605 --> 01:06:07,772
Are the officers who tortured you

859
01:06:07,772 --> 01:06:09,805
present in this courtroom, Mr. Lee Seong Jin?

860
01:06:09,805 --> 01:06:11,772
Even if it costs me my life,

861
01:06:11,772 --> 01:06:13,972
I'll make them pay for their crimes.

862
01:06:13,972 --> 01:06:16,105
I intend to reveal
who was involved in this case.

863
01:06:16,105 --> 01:06:18,338
[Media that broadcasts the essence
by cutting out the noise, Noise Cut]

864
01:06:18,338 --> 01:06:19,572
How can you do this to me?

865
01:06:19,572 --> 01:06:22,005
Do you even know what I've done?

866
01:06:22,005 --> 01:06:24,805
I'll give that answer in court.

